      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — centrifugal pump rotating domain",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.2M cells) performed on the rotating impeller domain. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI of 6.4% for hemolysis index on the fine mesh. Convergence achieved for bulk flow quantities; near-wall shear stress in blade tip clearance shows oscillatory behaviour on all mesh levels, flagged as unresolved discretisation uncertainty contributing to hemolysis prediction error.",
      "validationMetric": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI)",
      "comparisonOutcome": "Partial — bulk quantities converged, tip-clearance shear stress unconverged"
    }
  ],
